There is no razor like a Leaf Razor. Easier, safer & faster to use than traditional safety razors. Closer-shaving, more adjustable, & less wasteful than 5-blade cartridge razors. This eco-favorite has changed the game for hundreds of thousands of shavers, and it's ready for you. Most loved by head and body shavers.

Kick your skincare and makeup game up a notch with Leaf Dermaplaner, revealing smoother, glowing skin. Never toss another plastic facial razor or at-home dermaplaning head in the trash again. You'll be surprised at how effective a Leaf Shave tool can be ‚ô•

It's pretty simple, we thought that we could make a better razor and we were just a little crazy enough to try. 

Hi, I'm Adam, one of the founders at Leaf Shave. This is The Leaf razor, our triple-blade pivoting head all metal razor. It's like a hybrid between classic safety razors and modern cartridge systems. This razor in particular is most loved by body shavers and head shavers. If you shave your face, check out our single-edge razors Twig and Thorn!

With The Leaf razor, you'll load the steel blades as the refills. They're not encased in plastic, so if you care to reduce your plastic consumption - this is one of the best ways to do that. More than 2 billion plastic-razors are tossed each year.

The handle is going to cost more upfront then you might be used to, this one retails for $84. This does include free shipping, and a lifetime warranty, but it's still a bit much at first glance. 

That's why I wanted to draw your attention to the *true* cost of shaving. Which is the cost of refills. "Big Shave" and those fancy shave clubs want to lock you into their proprietary blade systems where you're constantly replacing the refills for dollars each. Forever. This can cost a hundred dollars a year, for decades. It ads up.

With Leaf, you can use any standard safety razor blade! There are dozens of different manufacturers of these blades. They've been in production for more than a century. They're high quality, and importantly they're VERY inexpensive. So we don't lock you into any proprietary ecosystem. You're free! You'll drop your yearly refill costs to a few dollars a year. The savings are actually pretty crazy.

So, I hope this helps. If you have any questions, pop them into the comments. We're always here to help if we can. - Adam @ leafshave.com
